snippet.textDisplay:
Billie Eilish just doesn't do it for me. I think it's because she feels like a deliberate "Not Like Other Girls" creation rather than something authentic. Like, she is the natural result of all the memes about girls loving true crime and chicken nuggets. It's kind of like when Nirvana burst onto the scene and had that persona of, "We're just a bunch of frustrated losers from a small town, and we despise our fame," except I actually believed Nirvana.

Don't inundate me with hate, Billie stans. She's very talented, and I'm sure YOU believe she's authentic, and that's cool with me. Honestly I probably would've loved her if she came out when I was a teen/tween.
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: Billie Eilish is the thing I get the least and I’m 23. Frankly, I think the thing that I get the least is what it has to do with or how it overlaps with alternative culture or why most sources that I see cover it or want to talk about it really do so. I don’t think I’m trying to not see the appeal or overtly wanting to deliberately dislike it either, but I don’t see the quality of songs or knockout moments or pop being done to such a high standard to push it over the edge. It’s not trying to dislike it, it’s not even really disliking it or if it is it’s not a very strong one, I just feel like I do not see it at all.
